<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Remarks</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Rhus integrifolia </i>is an aromatic, evergreen shrub with bright green leaves and reddish twigs found commonly along the frost-free coastlines of southern California. Plants are partially dioecious with either bisexual or unisexual flowers. Fruits are red, hairy, and sticky drupes. Small mammals and birds disperse the seeds (Lloret and Zedler 1991, Schmidt 1980). Shrubs are shade tolerant. Other trees and shrubs act as nurse plants, moderating environmental conditions and offering seedlings and saplings protection. Stands along the immediate coast occupy steep slopes and bluffs, especially on sandstone and conglomerate substrates. </div>
</div>

    
	
	
